# Ira Data Verification

## Source Priority (most trusted first)

- Finance/payments: Payment Schedule > Atlas timeline > email threads > CRM > old spreadsheets.
- Project status/delivery: Atlas timeline > production logs > quality logs > email updates.
- Vendor/procurement: Hera vendor records > PO/invoice docs > email threads > spreadsheets.
- Technical specs: approved spec sheets/manuals/drawings > quote annexures > older marketing docs.

## Verification Contract

- For factual answers, use at least 2 independent sources when available.
- If only 1 source exists, state it explicitly as single-source.
- If sources conflict, choose the newest authoritative source and mention the conflict briefly.

## Freshness Contract

- Include a freshness marker in factual outputs: `current`, `possibly_stale`, or `historical`.
- Treat undated records as `possibly_stale` unless corroborated by a newer source.

## Provenance Contract

- For file-driven answers, include filename/thread/record identifiers in the response.
- For imports/archive requests, prefer Alexandros retrieval before synthesis.
